headlines.description: — DeMar DeRozan scored 16 of his 36 points in the fourth quarter and the Chicago Bulls beat the Detroit Pistons 114-108 on Wednesday night to snap a five-game losing streak.
headlines.shortLinkText: DeRozan has big 4th quarter, helps Bulls snap losing streak

headlines.description: — Not that there was any doubt about this, but the Phoenix Suns are going to the playoffs.
headlines.shortLinkText: Booker has 23 points in return, Suns roll past Heat 111-90

headlines.description: — Giannis Antetokounmpo had 43 points and 12 rebounds and the Milwaukee Bucks beat the Atlanta Hawks 124-115 on Wednesday night for their sixth straight victory.
headlines.shortLinkText: Antetokounmpo scores 43 points, Bucks hold off Hawks 124-115

events.name: Los Angeles Lakers at Houston Rockets

headlines.description: — Rookie Jalen Green scored a career-high 32 points, including 10 in overtime, and the Houston Rockets outlasted the slumping Los Angeles Lakers for a 139-130 win Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Rookie Green has 32 as Rockets down Lakers in OT, 139-130

events.name: Oklahoma City Thunder at Minnesota Timberwolves

headlines.description: — Malik Beasley made 11 3-pointers to set a Timberwolves franchise-record and finished with 33 points to help lift Minnesota to its sixth win in a row with a 132-102 victory over the Oklahoma City Thunder on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Beasley sets T-Wolves 3-point mark in 132-102 win over OKC

events.name: Orlando Magic at New Orleans Pelicans

headlines.description: — Cole Anthony scored 19 points, Gary Harris added 16 in a reserve role, and the Orlando Magic beat the New Orleans Pelicans 108-102 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Cole, Harris lead Magic to 108-102 win over Pelicans

events.name: New York Knicks at Dallas Mavericks

headlines.description: — Julius Randle scored 26 points against his hometown team and the New York Knicks won for the fifth consecutive time in Dallas, blowing out the Mavericks 107-77 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Randle, Knicks win in Dallas again, blowing out Mavs 107-77

events.name: Toronto Raptors at San Antonio Spurs

headlines.description: — Fred VanVleet had 26 points and the Toronto Raptors beat the San Antonio Spurs 119-104 on Wednesday night, delaying Gregg Popovich’s coronation as the winningest coach in NBA history.
headlines.shortLinkText: VanVleet, Raptors delay Popovich's record in win over Spurs

events.name: Portland Trail Blazers at Utah Jazz

headlines.description: — Bojan Bogdanovic scored 27 points, hitting six 3-pointers, to lead the Utah Jazz to a 123-85 victory over the Portland Trail Blazers on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jazz dominate Trail Blazers for eighth straight home victory

headlines.description: — Nikola Jokic had 38 points, 18 rebounds and seven assists, and the Denver Nuggets held on after blowing an 18-point lead and beat the Sacramento Kings 106-100 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jokic dominates Kings as Nuggets win after blowing big lead

headlines.description: — Reggie Jackson and the Los Angeles Clippers didn't need the second-biggest comeback in NBA history to beat the Washington Wizards on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Clippers rally past Wizards again for 115-109 victory
